The paper deals with hardness assumptions and reductions for graph expansion problems, which are central topics in computational complexity theory and graph theory. The paper also mentions the Unique Games Conjecture, which is a well-known open problem in theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
